<br>
I highly doubt it.  Looks to me to be a raid zone.<br>
<br>
-Maidens Eye/Akheva... tried soloing here some but again it didn't seem like the best setup any suggestions?<br>
<br>
Tough racket solo.  Some mobs can be soloed without major difficulty.  Relatively low resists, so rains work well here.  Trains are a way of life, and adds are all too common.  This is best approached as an outdoor grouping zone.  If you solo at all, you would be best to pull lower level Gorangas either to zone or near zone, away from wanderers, chain pets, or maybe rain em to death.  Toilers can be soloed, but trying to single pull toilers to a place with no adds is very very difficult.  There may yet be a way to do it, though.<br>
<br>
- The Gray, tried soloing here some, but it didn't seem like the best setup really, but I may have been doing it wrong, any suggestions?<br>
<br>
